We define FE as the percentage of electron that has been used to reduce N2 and CO2 to form microbial biomass and secreted ammonia. The FE is calculated as follows:6FE=F3ΔTNbio×Vwirearray+ΔTNmedium×VmediumMN+4ΔTOCbio×VwirearrayMCi×A×t×100%\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
